wikipedia_page.main: Nathaniel Mayer Victor Rothschild, 3rd Baron Rothschild  (31 October 1910 – 20 March 1990) was a British banker, scientist, intelligence officer during World War II, and later a senior executive with Royal Dutch Shell and N M Rothschild & Sons, and an advisor to the Edward Heath and Margaret Thatcher governments of the UK.  He was a member of the prominent Rothschild family.
